 style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pzeReJV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bC5gXHH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BVagoBK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IN0usM2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jjFnbqM.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Fun stuff.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/DFlwumb</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[deafkitten]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Can Imgur help me in remembering my brother?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/cdjY05Z</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IqlLLEU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I lost my brother last weekend...
He was severely disabled with epilepsy, but he was always happy and laughing. His condition was chronic so over the years he lost the ability to walk and talk. And yet he was always full of joy; grinning and laughing when you would talk to him. He would smack things with his hand as a way of interacting with his surroundings so we would have lots of fun doing high-fives.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HANG5Ba.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Its hard looking back on all the memories, but I know its really important to process through the grief. I know Imgur is a big mix of lots of beliefs and backgrounds; my family is Christian and it helps to picture him in Heaven in a healed and healthy body. When he was in hospice, I kept imagining him being able to run through green fields and play and laugh. The Bible talks about the Earth being redeemed and being made perfect again (we can all agree things are pretty messed up now, right) so its nice to think about him enjoying Heaven by doing all the things he wasn't able to in this life.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tNk8qcL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>There are so many talented artists on here so I was hoping I could get some help with making a memorial picture/painting of him. I have this image of him laughing and running through green, grassy fields. Would any artistic imgurians be willing to help me make a painting that I can remember him by? 

I have included some pictures from his life that I hope will help. If more would be useful, I am currently going through our old photos and making digital copies. Hopefully, I will have more soon. 

Thanks in advance</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1I80Vv4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xebcX0H.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KBpgsp7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6p3uxDp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NXq1cMF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nqQlkIl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/krVr0zB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IVaKAIV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SrMgRKQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>See you on the other side Mathew!

EDIT: Wow, thank you everyone for your support and kind words! I am so happy to see that Matthew's smile continues to reach out and brighten people's day even after he is gone! Its so heartwarming to know that this community can carry on his memory!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cdjY05Z</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[chillychiweenie]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Andy Wahlberg</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9zLhaKm</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bpkpX9d.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9zLhaKm</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ikeepgettingbanned2]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>F*ck you ancestors we have KFC and weed vape pens</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/kLMXZUU</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/m46SlqZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/kLMXZUU</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[trustfallaccident]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>[Pixie and Brutus] Forgiveness</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bArFJIv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QvH2gWb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Source: Pet_Foolery on https://www.webtoons.com/en/challenge/pixie-and-brutus/mistake-part-1/viewer?title_no=452175&episode_no=107</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5ok8Q89.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bArFJIv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[RuneClaw]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Marley the painting penguin</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/aKs2C1c</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tELvZ3l.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Moody Gardens, Galvest